items.name: SorcererDraw Style - BETA
items.description:
Welcome all, hope you enjoy beta version of SorcererDraw style.

Came to this style after prompting some new and usual keywords, with some LoRA's merging their weights. This is a cute drawing style, it's not anime or manga, and it's not like others i saw.

This model is trained on my own realistic mix (SorcererMixC5 - unreleased), so it gives the intended style on realistic models, but also works giving style on others.

Currently advices:
- Works better on CLIP skip 2-3.
- 1.0 weight may produce artifacts, try 0.6 - 0-9 weights.
- Use some anime VAE like orangemix or the regular anime vae.
- Works better on realistic models, or at least is more noticeable.
- Works better on low CFG (<7)
- I think works better on shorter prompts.
- Works better on steps from 14 to 20.
- Restore faces doesn't work good here, but inpainting face at 0.2 - 0.5 at full res do the thing

Useful tags if you want: drawing style, thick lines drawing, old draw


Since this is a beta version, I would appreciate any feedback or testing on weights, CFG, steps, samplers, models... in order to improve next versions.

items.name: Benito Mussolini
items.description:
Benito Mussolini LoCon

IMPORTANT NOTES:

>This model is NOT meant to share or glorify any political view.

>Trigger word: "BenitoMussolini". Recommended weight: 0.7

>Trained on mostly b&w pictures, in order to get good results appropriate prompting and model is required.

>The best results achieved with realistic models (tested with Realistic Vision).

>Probably the easiest way is to just use inpaint.

>This time I’m testing LoCon, feel free to post your feedback.

Prompting

>Highly recommended to add this to your prompt:

Positive: in color

Negative: oversaturated, comics, fake, black and white, b&w, blurry, image noise, simple background, monochrome, (scar)

>Trained mostly on upper body pictures, might be hard to get full body.

>Negative prompts are powerful, use them to your advantage.

>I suggest using 768x768 resolution.

How to make a similar model

I know this model is far from being great, but if someone wants to know the workflow, here you go:

1. Find good images and crop them. 2. Upscale x2~x4 (in my case mostly R-ESRGAN). 3. Remove noise using any graphic software. 4. Scale down. 5. Train LoCon (using Google Colab, e.g. Kohya Trainer). 6. This time I’ve experimented with block weight adjusting (check out sd-webui-lora-block-weight and sd-webui-supermerger awesome tools for LoRa fine tuning)

I mostly use b&w photos, so following steps 2,3,4 leads to significant increase of quality and reduction of image noise.

Also:

>Why do you share such controversial models?

Mainly for fun, also because I can as it’s allowed and I’m not doing anything illegal.

>If you want to use my model anywhere feel free to do so, but it would be nice to put me in credits.

items.name: Mistoon_Sapphire
items.description:
You can now get all my LoRAs in one single package if you subscribe to my Patreon (including those not on CivitAI):

The Complete Catalog Download | Patreon

Mistoon_Sapphire is a variant of my SD model Mistoon_Anime that tries to achieve a more "2.5d" style while still mantaining some resemblance to the modern anime style.

The starting point for this model was my blend. From there, I then added a few of my custom LoRAs in the mix to change the esthetic.

This merge has been created using a lot of different models. In the start I've used popular models (and also nieche ones), but now I'm mostly using my custom LoRAs to finetune the model in the way I like.

This model is oriented towards creating girl portraits, but the V2 is also capable of creating male characters in a convincing way.

Inpainting version coming SOON.

There are other 4 variants of this model available, check out my profile:

The idea behind Mistoon_Sapphire is to achieve the 2.5d style without losing the original anime style and colors.

It creates realistic and expressive characters with a "cartoony" twist. Unlike other anime models that tend to have muted or dark colors, Mistoon_Sapphire uses bright and vibrant colors to make the characters stand out.

This model can easily do both SFW and NSFW stuff

The v1 version is the original Mistoon_Sapphire that a lot of you already know. It's detailed but still colorful. If you've never used the original version I highly recommend to check out the gallery and see if it is for you. If you want to use the V1 you'll need a VAE, I highly suggest you to use this one.

For those who have already used my model, the newest version:

  • Is WAY better at producing images depicting males

  • Has lower distortion at lower resolutions

  • Is way more detailed

  • Has better backgrounds consistency

  • Eyes are more detailed and consistent

  • Is incredibly detailed when working with close-ups or upper body portrait

  • Is better with NSFW than the previous version

  • Works better with CLIP skip set to 2

  • Has already a VAE embedded.

In the past few months I've had a lot of people asking me why their pictures are not as detailed or clean as mine. I've written a few articles about SD, but if you want to learn my exact workflow I highly recommend you to check out my latest one: My Workflow

If you want to test this (or other models), I have made an extension to help me create pictures using a variety of different tags. The previews images have been generated using my custom extension Ranbooru which scrapes tags from random images on gelbooru, safebooru and rule34.

items.name: Hitomi T
items.description:
Background:

This Textual Inversion embedding bears a striking resemblance to a famous JAV Actress with world-renowned assets.

Trained using base SD1.5 on 50 high quality 512x512 cropped images of the subject "modeling" with text removed from the images. The embedding is 16 tokens--that seems excessive, but it's the only way I got good results.

I'm very new to this, and I've found that training is, unfortunately, an art, not a science. So, this embedding isn't perfect and has some limitations. Please keep that in mind when you rate!

Note: Remove the ".zip" from the end of the file name and place in the embeddings folder. The default trigger is 1hit1.

Important Points:

  • For whatever reason, the embedding works worse for realistic generations and on the base SD1.5 model. Other models and artistic styles produce better results.

  • The results get much better with prompt engineering and, especially, lengthy prompts.

  • You definitely have to adjust the weight of the trigger word relative to the rest of the prompt.

  • Generations of the subject's assets can be prone to distortions, especially when they are exposed. This doesn't occur often, but does happen. I believe this was due to the fact that the extreme size of those assets made it impossible to fit both them and the subject's face in a close-up when cropping to a square image. This seems to be mitigated by using words in the prompt to describe those assets.

  • You will need to include words like naked, nude, and topless in the negative prompt to avoid accidental wardrobe malfunctions (we wouldn't want that, now would we?).

  • I've found that including open mouth and teeth in the negative prompt improves generations.

  • Unless you include strong and specific descriptions of your intended background scenery or setting in your prompts, generations will tend to incorporate the following elements: palm trees, desert plants, brick walls, distant buildings, sunny weather, and the interior of houses. Prompting for background scenery and setting elements seems to mitigate this effect.

  • For further tips & tricks, see the PNG info in the sample images. Yes, my prompting style is weird and complicated, but it works, right?

Samples:

These sample generations were done in Galaxy Time Machine Photo for You and Deliberate. The crappier looking ones were made using simple prompts; the better looking ones required extensive prompt engineering. I didn't use HiRes Fix, Face Restoration, ControlNet, Img2Img, Lycoris, or Negative Embeddings on any of these generations. I believe I used model LORAs on a few, but none for concepts or subjects. Your results will probably improve if you use any of those!

Note: The new religious image I uploaded uses a lot of tricks. Oh, also, the one demon picture uses a ton of stuff too. Just showing what it's possible to do with the embedding and some extreme engineering.

PREVIEW

I've been working on Version 2 and had a breakthrough--it was leaps and bounds better than Version 1... but, after playing around with it more, there were some inconsistencies with generation. When it worked, it worked much better, but it was way more difficult to prompt for. Basically, unless you prompted for specific "features" of the subject, they wouldn't show up well.

I'm going to try fixing what I think the issue was (likely captioning) and try training again sometime soon. My hope is that I can produce an embedding that gets results as good as the one below with simpler prompts and more consistency.

modelVersions.name: v1.10
modelVersions.description:
Hitomi T - Version 1.10:

  • Trigger Word: 8hit8

  • Rename 8hit8.pt.zip to 8hit8.pt and place in the embeddings directory

The new version of my Hitomi T textual inversion embedding is finally out! It solves some of the issues with my last embedding, but does admittedly have some of its own, as noted below.

I'm still new at this and I'm always learning, so feel free to drop me some tips and tricks. I suspect that the issues I'm having with getting a consistent likeness during generations are related to my dataset somehow.

Note: Some of the preview images use a different trigger word for the embedding. This is not because it's a different version of the embedding, but because I was changing the embedding name as I was training and testing. In order to replicate the previews, you will need to change the trigger to 8hit8 in the prompt.

Improvements Over Version 1.0:

  • When the embedding gets good results, it seems like it gets a much closer likeness.

  • Results seem to default to a more photorealistic style, i.e., they are more detailed regardless of other style prompting. So, if you prompt for a fantasy style painting, it will still look like a painting in that style, but with finer intricacies than if you just prompted using something like "woman."

  • Background elements from the dataset, i.e., desert plants and stone walls, no longer subtly influence generations.

  • It's much easier to change things like clothing, poses, and hair styles on the subject.

  • It seems to be easier to get the subject to keep their clothing on.

Challenges and Caveats:

  • For whatever reason, the embedding works worse for realistic generations and on the base SD1.5 model. Other models and artistic styles produce better results.

  • The subject's assets might not be distorted as much as in Version 1.0; however, the size isn't as true-to-life. You might need to prompt about those assets to make them an appropriate size. This doesn't seem to be much of an issue, but it still seems to crop up.

  • The likeness seems to blend very easily if you prompt for other people or types of people, i.e., "basketball player." Facial features will blend and not resemble the subject as much.

  • As such, you might have to mess around with the weight of the trigger word more in order to maintain a good likeness, moreso than in Version 1.0.

  • This embedding still favors lengthier and more complex prompts.

  • There seem to be more frequent issues with hands, specifically fingernails. I would recommend using negative prompts and embeddings to correct hand issues.

  • You still need to use negative prompts to get the subject to keep their clothing on, i.e., "naked," "topless," and "nudity."

  • For further tips & tricks, see the PNG info in the sample images. Yes, my prompting style is weird and complicated, but it works, right?

Sample Generations:

These sample generations were done in Galaxy Time Machine Photo for You. I didn't use HiRes Fix, ControlNet, Img2Img, Lora, Lycoris, or Negative Embeddings on any of these generations. I did use Face Restoration on a few.

The Future:

I would like to improve the consistency of generations with a good likeness, but I've hit a bit of a wall. If anyone has any tips to resolve this issue, please let me know. I'm still a beginner and have lots of room for improvement!

modelVersions.name: v1
modelVersions.description:
• Trained on the old version of kohya-LoRA-dreambooth on Google Colab.

    • 45 epochs, 1 batch.

    • 1 repeats

  • cosine scheduler, 130 lr_warmup_steps.

  • 128 net_alpha, 128 net_dim.

  • Training resolution 896x896.

  • Model: NAI Model (animefull-final-pruned.ckpt), no VAE.

  • 150 max_token_length.

  • fp16 mixed_precision.

items.name: Uta no Princess-sama BACK TO THE IDOL Flower Candy LoRAs
items.description:
These three idols forming a unit called Flower Candy all came from a joke website made by Broccoli and Elements Garden during April 1st for a fake male focused spin-off from their fujoshi idol franchise called Uta no Prince-sama. It had fake Twitter accounts, a fake member audition announcement for Flower Candy idols (ironically Silent Queen unit already had proper idols voicing each three characters while Flower Candy ones didn't despite having a short 3D PV video of them, hilarious right?) and two videos for each idol units (Silent Queen units weren't possible to train since they each only had two 2D drawings compared to Flower Candy who also had a 3D PV video which was essential for me when training all three of them since they came out better when I screenshot 'em multiple times).

Here's prompts for each idols:

Suzu Hanamichi:

suzu hanamichi, school uniform, (beige jacket, long sleeves, white dress shirt, blue bowtie, blue plaid skirt), (thighhighs, white legwear), black loafers / idol, waitress, pink dress, short sleeves, waist apron, name tag, black footwear

Otoha Hiiragi:

otoha hiiragi, school uniform, beige jacket, open jacket, long sleeves, blue cardigan, red bowtie, blue pleated skirt, black pantyhose, black loafers / idol, waitress, blue dress, short sleeves, waist apron, name tag, black footwear

Ruri Sakurada:

ruri sakurada, twin braids, school uniform, (beige cardigan), long sleeves, (green bowtie), blue plaid skirt, (green socks), loafers / idol, waitress, yellow dress, short sleeves, waist apron, name tag, black footwear

items.name: Seraphina - Disgaea 5
items.description:
I love the Disgaea franchise (even the newest 3d one) and I had a ton of fun playing the 5th version. So, I decided to make a Lora for Seraphina from D5. It was trained on animefull_final with 29 images with the usual self-pruning and tagging. I like keeping my prompts simple for the first few pictures so that you can see it without a whole bunch of mumbo jumbo. Make your pictures better than mine though!

What does it do you ask? A Lora of Seraphina from Disgaea 5 with her outfit from the game.

How to use it: This one turned out a little weird in terms of weight. Strength of 1 is fine if you just want her usual outfit. I would highly recommend a weight of 0.5 to 0.7 otherwise. if you want to adjust her more. I should fix that in a V2. Also the trigger word is:

SeraphinaD5 - Only trigger word currently added.

Extra, Extra!: Should be well trained and usable in most models. Images shown for example.

Picture Descriptions:

1-3: AnythingV3 using just this Lora. (First image I had to remove a 3rd hand with photoshop so it's missing the generation data :( ).

4: AnythingV3 with her wearing a doctor outfit.

5: AnythingV3 combo'd with my in progress V2 Corruption Locon.

6: AnythingV3 combo'd with my released Bimbo Locon

7: AnythingV3 combo'd with my in progress Angelify Locon

8-9: AnythingV3 combo'd with my in progress Brainwashing Locon. (I had to inpaint out a random hand at the top left/top right of each image because the fingers were too messed up lol).

10: AbyssOrange using just this Lora.

11: PerfectWorld using just this Lora.

What's next for this? A v2 where you don't need the weights as low for adjustments.

What's next that isn't this?

More character Loras. (Ghislaine from Mushoku Tensei, Conqueror Lilias from E7, Catherine from Catherine Full Body, Miku + Piscalat from Idaten Deities, Kuribayashi Shino from GATE, Rin Sohma from Fruits Basket, "Kasumi" from P5, Ann from P5, Ikumi Mito from Food Wars, Alice Nakiri from Food Wars, Chika Fujiwara from Kaguya-sama, Lulu from FF10, Momo from My Hero, Vivy from Vivy, Dominique de Sade from Vanitas, and Dos from One Punch Man.) And maybe Wilhelm van Astrea, my favorite Re:Zero husbando or a Prinny from Disgaea.

V2's of some of the previous Loras. Specifically make them more diversely acceptable with other models and LORA's.

I also have some more quite NSFW Locon's. Specifically, being pet play, being stepped on, brainwashing, corruptedv2, and one that might be too much for me to even upload here >.<.

And, uh, I want to make a few happy Locon's so I have an "angel-ify" your character one coming up. And a forest fairy one as well. And a soldier one. And a barbarian one.

Or just give me some random suggestion or priority opinions. That works too.

items.name: Shifty (NIKKE: Goddess Of Victory)
items.description:
When I saw gameplay videos of the NPC secretary from NIKKE whom for one day became playable for a special event during April 1st, I had to train a LoRA of her ASAP regardless of her current obscurity due to her design and personality. She didn't have the ability to die at all since she had Godmode on apparently making her health reset to full once depleted each time and her Burst ability when she shoots with a minigun with projectiles bouncing all over the place due to her unept ability as an actual NIKKE unit, would hope one day to see her as an actual playable unit albeit without Godmode and a more proper Burst ability.

Here's prompt for her:

shifty, animal ear headphones, fake animal ears, hair ornament, blue dress, white sailor collar, short sleeves, blue necktie, wrist cuffs, white skirt

I made her flexible for any other kinds of costumes like with my other LoRAs, however due to her very low dataset, some elements of her costume might bake their way in and strangely backgrounds would look messy if I generate at 1.0 strength, 0.8 seems to generate without problems at all more or less...

items.name: Annette (Spy Kyoshitsu/Classroom)
items.description:
When I recently discovered this character from Spy Kyoshitsu, (Spy Classroom) which finished airing an anime season while the LN is still ongoing (at the time of writing this), having my same birthdate besides a tendency to forget stuff frequently and getting excited for lots of s*** in just like her, I knew I had to train a LoRA of her.

I screenshot her in almost every scene from all episodes of the anime adaptation (besides grabbing the usual official drawings and fan arts of her) in order to ensure she came out perfectly when training her and I think I made a job well done at that, I trained her with three costumes:

Her default one:

annette (boga), default, twintails, eyepatch, mini hat, black headwear, military uniform, black dress, epaulettes, long sleeves, buttons, frills, black boots

Lamplight school uniform:

annette (boga), eyepatch, twintails, lamplight, school uniform, pinafore dress, brown vest, white shirt, long sleeves, red bow, black socks, loafers

Her blue dress she wore in the 3rd episode of the anime (since I personally quite liked it a lot):

annette (boga), eyepatch, twintails, episode3, school uniform, blue dress, short sleeves, red bowtie, long skirt, pleated skirt

Her eyepatch isn't baked/pruned so you can generate her without it if you wish, if you still see it generated, try putting eyepatch tag in negative prompt.

items.name: Pronebone (Side View)
items.description:
This is a LoRA to generate Pronebone (Side View).

  • I suggest using this at 0.8-1.0 weight for best results but make sure to always play around with the weight.

  • It was generated and only tested using AOM2, AOM3 A1, My Own Mix, OrangeMix VAE and AnythingV3 VAE.

  • Always add this to the prompt to activate it: proneposition, prone bone, 1boy, ass, lying, sex from behind

  • It was trained on 512x512 - so, I suggest generating in 512x512 then upscaling to an higher resolution.

You can make small variations by adding these tags individually or together.

Note: Some of these will break generations or enhance them, depending on what tags you're putting together.

  • From Side - will force the generations to be fully to the side and add variations.

  • Breast Press - will press her breasts against the ground, bed, etc.

  • Pillow, Pillow Hug - will wrap her arms around a pillow and add those variations.

  • Motion lines - will add the effect of motion in the image or at least the motion lines.

  • Fat Man - will replace the muscular man with a fatter man.

  • Grabbing, Grabbing another's hair - will attempt to place the man's hand on her head.

Known Issues (As far as I know)

  • Sometimes the man won't be generated but his arms will be or the man just won't generate at all.

  • Sometimes the generation will be DEFORMED because it's trying to force two variations through the universal tag.

  • Almost every picture in the dataset - The girl is bottomless, so it struggles adding legwear (shorts, pants, panties).

Follow me on Twitter for updates- https://twitter.com/TrueHeroBang

Everything I'm making will always be free but if you want to show a little bit more support, you can buy me a coffee - https://ko-fi.com/ekune
